                    %h1 Formatting Codes
                :markdown
                    Text formatting codes are used to create fancy colorized text, they are prefixed with either a `` ` or a `§`. After using a formatting code such as `§o` (italic) it has to be reset, otherwise it will continue until the end of the text.

                    `NOTE:` It is recommended that the same formatting code prefix is used in the whole XML file.

                    Examples

                        <!-- Using ` as the formatting code prefix -->
                        <item name="`iFrozen `rWater">snowball</item>
                        
                        <!-- Using § as the formatting code prefix -->
                        <line>This is one of three of §9Blue Team§r's victory monuments.</line>
                        <item name="§1Blue §4Red §rNone">book</item>

